# Local tool configuration and state
.kimi/
.specify/
KIMI.md

# Pre-push hook multi-mirror dedup cache (advisory; recreated on demand).
# Forensic anchor: SP-3a Step 6+7 used --no-verify on 3-of-4 mirror
# pushes because re-running scripts/ci.sh --changed-only against an
# identical SHA was redundant. The hook now caches verified SHAs in
# this file and skips Layer 2 on cache hit. Local-only by design.
.lava-ci-evidence/.pre-push-verified-shas

# Timestamped scripts/ci.sh run-output dirs are local session telemetry,
# not committed evidence. The committed evidence files live at the
# top level of .lava-ci-evidence/ and in named subdirs (sp3a-*/, sp2-*/,
# bluff-hunt/, sixth-law-incidents/, Lava-Android-*/).
.lava-ci-evidence/2026-*/

# Build outputs at any depth (already covered for /build but nested
# modules generate their own build/ dirs)
**/build/
.env.*
.env.local

# === Firebase artifacts (added 2026-05-05) ===
# google-services.json contains the project's web API key — technically
# public per Firebase's threat model, but gitignored by project convention
# (see root CLAUDE.md §6.H: credentials never in tracked files).
app/google-services.json
**/google-services.json

# Firebase Web SDK config for Go API (firebase-web-config.json).
# Contains apiKey, authDomain, projectId, etc. — public-facing per
# Firebase's threat model but gitignored by convention.
lava-api-go/firebase-web-config.json

# Firebase Admin SDK service account key — HIGHLY SENSITIVE.
# This is a long-lived credential that grants server-side access
# to ALL Firebase services for the project. NEVER commit.
lava-api-go/firebase-admin-key.json
firebase-admin-key.json
**/firebase-admin-*.json

# Firebase debug log can leak request bodies including project IDs,
# OAuth tokens, etc. Local-only.
firebase-debug.log
**/firebase-debug.log

# Firebase App Distribution upload reports — local telemetry.
.firebase/
firebase-distribute-*.log

# Phase 11: build-time generated lava.auth.LavaAuthGenerated source
app/build/generated/lava-auth/
